Dozens of civilians have been killed or injured in a terrorist attack in north-west Chinaâ€™s Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region. The attack took place in Shache County of Kashgar Prefecture early Monday morning.
A gang armed with knives attacked a police station and government offices in Elixku Township, and some moved on to the nearby Huangdi Township, attacking civilians and smashing vehicles as they passed. Dozens of Uygur and Han civilians were killed or injured.
Police officers at the scene shot dead dozens of the attackers. Thirty one cars were smashed, six of them were set on fire. Police say initial investigations shows it was an premeditated terrorist attack. Further investigations are underway.



